  "prompt": "What should be my daily schedule?",
  "response": "Creating a daily schedule can greatly enhance your productivity and well-being. Below is a general framework that you can customize based on your personal goals, commitments, and lifestyle:\n\n### Sample Daily Schedule\n\n#### Morning\n- **6:00 AM - 7:00 AM**: **Wake Up & Morning Routine**\n  - Drink a glass of water\n  - Stretch or do light exercise (yoga, jogging, etc.)\n  - Shower and get dressed\n\n- **7:00 AM - 7:30 AM**: **Breakfast**\n  - Eat a healthy breakfast (protein, whole grains, fruits)\n\n- **7:30 AM - 8:00 AM**: **Plan Your Day**\n  - Review your to-do list\n  - Set priorities for the day\n\n#### Mid-Morning\n- **8:00 AM - 12:00 PM**: **Focused Work/Study Time**\n  - Tackle your most important tasks/projects\n  - Use techniques like the Pomodoro Technique (25 minutes focused work, 5 minutes break)\n\n#### Lunch\n- **12:00 PM - 1:00 PM**: **Lunch Break**\n  - Step away from your workspace\n  - Enjoy a healthy lunch and take a short walk if possible\n\n#### Afternoon\n- **1:00 PM - 3:00 PM**: **Continue Work/Study**\n  - Focus on secondary tasks\n  - Attend meetings or collaborate with others if needed\n\n- **3:00 PM - 3:15 PM**: **Short Break**\n  - Stand up, stretch, or take a quick walk\n\n- **3:15 PM - 5:00 PM**: **Wrap Up Work/Study**\n  - Finish any remaining tasks\n  - Organize your workspace for the next day\n\n#### Evening\n- **5:00 PM - 6:00 PM**: **Exercise**\n  - Go for a run, hit the gym, or do a home workout\n\n- **6:00 PM - 7:00 PM**: **Dinner**\n  - Enjoy a healthy dinner, ideally with family or friends\n\n- **7:00 PM - 8:00 PM**: **Relaxation/Personal Time**\n  - Read a book, watch a show, or engage in a hobby\n\n#### Night\n- **8:00 PM - 9:00 PM**: **Prepare for Tomorrow**\n  - Set goals for the next day\n  - Lay out clothes, pack lunch, etc.\n\n- **9:00 PM - 10:00 PM**: **Wind Down**\n  - Limit screen time, practice mindfulness, or journal\n  - Prepare for bed\n\n- **10:00 PM**: **Sleep**\n  - Aim for 7-9 hours of sleep.\n\n### Tips for Customization\n- **Identify Priorities**: Adjust time blocks based on what\u2019s most important for you (e.g., work, study, family time).\n- **Be Flexible**: Life can be unpredictable, so allow some flexibility in your schedule.\n- **Incorporate Breaks**: Regular breaks can help maintain focus and reduce fatigue.\n- **Review Weekly**: At the end of the week, review what worked and what didn\u2019t, and adjust accordingly.\n\nFeel free to modify this schedule to better fit your needs and lifestyle!",
